Package jetbrains.mps.openapi.editor.update

Interface Updater

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    UpdaterImpl
    public interface Updater
    This class is responsible for EditorComponent update and synchronization processes.

    The tree of currently visible EditorCells will be substituted completely or partually as a part of update process. Update process can be started as a result of explicit update() or flushModelEvents() method calls. Alternatively, it can be triggered as a consequence of arrived model notifications, listened by the Updater implementations.

    UpdaterListener.editorUpdateStarted(EditorComponent)/UpdaterListener.editorUpdated(EditorComponent) notifications should be fired at the very beginning of the update process and in the end of it.

    New instance of UpdateSession may be created and disposed during update process. Update process may include some other internal tasks except of EditorCell tree update (re-creation).

    It should be possible to execute update process as a part of another (currently running) editor update process for the same editor. In such cases Updater will fire the pair of UpdaterListener.editorUpdateStarted(EditorComponent)/ UpdaterListener.editorUpdated(EditorComponent) events only for top-level update process.

    Alternatively, Updater implementation may decide to synchronize some EditorCells with model information to reflect actual state of the model without starting complete editor update process. In this case UpdaterListener.cellSynchronizedWithModel(EditorCell) event will be fired.

    • Method Detail

      • update

        void update()
        This method should be used to force full update process of the associated editor content (tree of EditorCells)

        New UpdateSession instance will be created within this method and will be available via getCurrentUpdateSession() method until the end of update process, so it can be used from any code called as a sub-sequence of this method execution. E.g. the code generated from the editor aspect of any language.

        This method will set new rootCell for the associated EditorComponent.

        Internal update process-specific information about the model will be collected during this method execution and used later to update the editor incrementally.

      • getCurrentUpdateSession

        UpdateSession getCurrentUpdateSession()
        Return currently running update session or null if there is no active update session. UpdateSession will be created at the beginning of the rebuild process for the tree of EditorCells, as a sub-sequence of update process. UpdateSession will be stopped/disposed at the end of cell tree rebuild process.

        It's prohibited to execute another update before the end of currently running one. AssertionError will be thrown in such cases.

        Returns:
        currently running update session

      • setInitialEditorHints

        boolean setInitialEditorHints​(@Nullable
                              String[] hints)
        Use this method to specify initial set of editor hints used by updater process to create EditorCell tree for the current editor. If null specified then default project-wide hints settings will be used.

        Return boolean value reflecting the fact that list of initialEditorHints were updated, so client should call explicit editor update (rebuild editor) in order to refresh current editor in accordance.

        Parameters:
        hints - array of hints or null if default settings should be used
        Returns:
        true if set of initialEditorHints were updated
